112// Calls the given method with the provided arguments on all objects in the
113// collection.
114template <typename T, typename MethodPointer, typename... Args>
115void ForAll(const std::vector<T*>& objects, MethodPointer method,
116 const Args&... args) {
117 for (T* const object : objects) {
118 DCHECK(object != nullptr);
119 (object->*method)(args...);
120 }
121}

141 params.set_trace_search(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_trace_search));
142 params.set_name_all_variables(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_name_variables));
143 params.set_profile_file(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_profile_file));
144 params.set_profile_local_search(
145 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_print_local_search_profile));
146 params.set_print_local_search_profile(
147 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_print_local_search_profile));
148 params.set_print_model(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_print_model));
149 params.set_print_model_stats(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_model_stats));
150 params.set_disable_solve(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_disable_solve));
151 params.set_name_cast_variables(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_name_cast_variables));
152 params.set_print_added_constraints(
153 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_print_added_constraints));
154 params.set_use_small_table(absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_use_small_table));
155 params.set_use_cumulative_edge_finder(
156 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_use_cumulative_edge_finder));
157 params.set_use_cumulative_time_table(
158 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_use_cumulative_time_table));
159 params.set_use_cumulative_time_table_sync(
160 absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_use_cumulative_time_table_sync));

214void Demon::inhibit(Solver* const s) {
215 if (stamp_ < std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max()) {
216 s->SaveAndSetValue(&stamp_, std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max());
217 }
218}
219
220void Demon::desinhibit(Solver* const s) {
221 if (stamp_ == std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max()) {
222 s->SaveAndSetValue(&stamp_, s->stamp() - 1);
223 }
224}

226// ------------------ Queue class ------------------
227
228extern void CleanVariableOnFail(IntVar* var);
229
230class Queue {
231 public:
232 static constexpr int64_t kTestPeriod = 10000;
233
234 explicit Queue(Solver* const s)
235 : solver_(s),
236 stamp_(1),
237 freeze_level_(0),
238 in_process_(false),
239 clean_action_(nullptr),
240 clean_variable_(nullptr),
241 in_add_(false),
242 instruments_demons_(s->InstrumentsDemons()) {}
243
244 ~Queue() {}
245
246 void Freeze() {
247 freeze_level_++;
248 stamp_++;
249 }
250
251 void Unfreeze() {
252 if (--freeze_level_ == 0) {
253 Process();
254 }
255 }
256
257 void ProcessOneDemon(Demon* const demon) {
258 demon->set_stamp(stamp_ - 1);
259 if (!instruments_demons_) {
260 if (++solver_->demon_runs_[demon->priority()] % kTestPeriod == 0) {
261 solver_->TopPeriodicCheck();
262 }
263 demon->Run(solver_);
264 solver_->CheckFail();
265 } else {
266 solver_->GetPropagationMonitor()->BeginDemonRun(demon);
267 if (++solver_->demon_runs_[demon->priority()] % kTestPeriod == 0) {
268 solver_->TopPeriodicCheck();
269 }
270 demon->Run(solver_);
271 solver_->CheckFail();
272 solver_->GetPropagationMonitor()->EndDemonRun(demon);
273 }
274 }
275
276 void Process() {
277 if (!in_process_) {
278 in_process_ = true;
279 while (!var_queue_.empty() || !delayed_queue_.empty()) {
280 if (!var_queue_.empty()) {
281 Demon* const demon = var_queue_.front();
282 var_queue_.pop_front();
283 ProcessOneDemon(demon);
284 } else {
285 DCHECK(!delayed_queue_.empty());
286 Demon* const demon = delayed_queue_.front();
287 delayed_queue_.pop_front();
288 ProcessOneDemon(demon);
289 }
290 }
291 in_process_ = false;
292 }
293 }
294
295 void ExecuteAll(const SimpleRevFIFO<Demon*>& demons) {
296 if (!instruments_demons_) {
297 for (SimpleRevFIFO<Demon*>::Iterator it(&demons); it.ok(); ++it) {
298 Demon* const demon = *it;
299 if (demon->stamp() < stamp_) {
300 DCHECK_EQ(demon->priority(), Solver::NORMAL_PRIORITY);
301 if (++solver_->demon_runs_[Solver::NORMAL_PRIORITY] % kTestPeriod ==
302 0) {
303 solver_->TopPeriodicCheck();
304 }
305 demon->Run(solver_);
306 solver_->CheckFail();
307 }
308 }
309 } else {
310 for (SimpleRevFIFO<Demon*>::Iterator it(&demons); it.ok(); ++it) {
311 Demon* const demon = *it;
312 if (demon->stamp() < stamp_) {
313 DCHECK_EQ(demon->priority(), Solver::NORMAL_PRIORITY);
314 solver_->GetPropagationMonitor()->BeginDemonRun(demon);
315 if (++solver_->demon_runs_[Solver::NORMAL_PRIORITY] % kTestPeriod ==
316 0) {
317 solver_->TopPeriodicCheck();
318 }
319 demon->Run(solver_);
320 solver_->CheckFail();
321 solver_->GetPropagationMonitor()->EndDemonRun(demon);
322 }
323 }
324 }
325 }
326
327 void EnqueueAll(const SimpleRevFIFO<Demon*>& demons) {
328 for (SimpleRevFIFO<Demon*>::Iterator it(&demons); it.ok(); ++it) {
329 EnqueueDelayedDemon(*it);
330 }
331 }
332
333 void EnqueueVar(Demon* const demon) {
334 DCHECK(demon->priority() == Solver::VAR_PRIORITY);
335 if (demon->stamp() < stamp_) {
336 demon->set_stamp(stamp_);
337 var_queue_.push_back(demon);
338 if (freeze_level_ == 0) {
339 Process();
340 }
341 }
342 }
343
344 void EnqueueDelayedDemon(Demon* const demon) {
345 DCHECK(demon->priority() == Solver::DELAYED_PRIORITY);
346 if (demon->stamp() < stamp_) {
347 demon->set_stamp(stamp_);
348 delayed_queue_.push_back(demon);
349 }
350 }
351
352 void AfterFailure() {
353 // Clean queue.
354 var_queue_.clear();
355 delayed_queue_.clear();
356
357 // Call cleaning actions on variables.
358 if (clean_action_ != nullptr) {
359 clean_action_(solver_);
360 clean_action_ = nullptr;
361 } else if (clean_variable_ != nullptr) {
362 CleanVariableOnFail(clean_variable_);
363 clean_variable_ = nullptr;
364 }
365
366 freeze_level_ = 0;
367 in_process_ = false;
368 in_add_ = false;
369 to_add_.clear();
370 }
371
372 void increase_stamp() { stamp_++; }
373
374 uint64_t stamp() const { return stamp_; }
375
376 void set_action_on_fail(Solver::Action a) {
377 DCHECK(clean_variable_ == nullptr);
378 clean_action_ = std::move(a);
379 }
380
381 void set_variable_to_clean_on_fail(IntVar* var) {
382 DCHECK(clean_action_ == nullptr);
383 clean_variable_ = var;
384 }
385
386 void reset_action_on_fail() {
387 DCHECK(clean_variable_ == nullptr);
388 clean_action_ = nullptr;
389 }
390
391 void AddConstraint(Constraint* const c) {
392 to_add_.push_back(c);
393 ProcessConstraints();
394 }
395
396 void ProcessConstraints() {
397 if (!in_add_) {
398 in_add_ = true;
399 // We cannot store to_add_.size() as constraints can add other
400 // constraints. For the same reason a range-based for loop cannot be used.
401 // TODO(user): Make to_add_ a queue to make the behavior more obvious.
402 for (int counter = 0; counter < to_add_.size(); ++counter) {
403 Constraint* const constraint = to_add_[counter];
404 // TODO(user): Add profiling to initial propagation
405 constraint->PostAndPropagate();
406 }
407 in_add_ = false;
408 to_add_.clear();
409 }
410 }
411
412 private:
413 Solver* const solver_;
414 std::deque<Demon*> var_queue_;
415 std::deque<Demon*> delayed_queue_;
416 uint64_t stamp_;
417 // The number of nested freeze levels. The queue is frozen if and only if
418 // freeze_level_ > 0.
419 uint32_t freeze_level_;
420 bool in_process_;
421 Solver::Action clean_action_;
422 IntVar* clean_variable_;
423 std::vector<Constraint*> to_add_;
424 bool in_add_;
425 const bool instruments_demons_;
426};

509// ----- addrval struct -----
510
511// This template class is used internally to implement reversibility.
512// It stores an address and the value that was at the address.
513template <class T>
514struct addrval {
515 public:
516 addrval() : address_(nullptr) {}
517 explicit addrval(T* adr) : address_(adr), old_value_(*adr) {}
518 void restore() const { (*address_) = old_value_; }
519
520 private:
521 T* address_;
522 T old_value_;
523};

525// ----- Compressed trail -----
526
527// ---------- Trail Packer ---------
528// Abstract class to pack trail blocks.
529
530template <class T>
531class TrailPacker {
532 public:
533 explicit TrailPacker(int block_size) : block_size_(block_size) {}
534 virtual ~TrailPacker() {}
535 int input_size() const { return block_size_ * sizeof(addrval<T>); }
536 virtual void Pack(const addrval<T>* block, std::string* packed_block) = 0;
537 virtual void Unpack(const std::string& packed_block, addrval<T>* block) = 0;
538
539 private:
540 const int block_size_;
541 DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(TrailPacker);
542};
543
544template <class T>
545class NoCompressionTrailPacker : public TrailPacker<T> {
546 public:
547 explicit NoCompressionTrailPacker(int block_size)
548 : TrailPacker<T>(block_size) {}
549 ~NoCompressionTrailPacker() override {}
550 void Pack(const addrval<T>* block, std::string* packed_block) override {
551 DCHECK(block != nullptr);
552 DCHECK(packed_block != nullptr);
553 absl::string_view block_str(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(block),
554 this->input_size());
555 packed_block->assign(block_str.data(), block_str.size());
556 }
557 void Unpack(const std::string& packed_block, addrval<T>* block) override {
558 DCHECK(block != nullptr);
559 memcpy(block, packed_block.c_str(), packed_block.size());
560 }
561
562 private:
563 DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(NoCompressionTrailPacker);
564};
565
566template <class T>
567class ZlibTrailPacker : public TrailPacker<T> {
568 public:
569 explicit ZlibTrailPacker(int block_size)
570 : TrailPacker<T>(block_size),
571 tmp_size_(compressBound(this->input_size())),
572 tmp_block_(new char[tmp_size_]) {}
573
574 ~ZlibTrailPacker() override {}
575
576 void Pack(const addrval<T>* block, std::string* packed_block) override {
577 DCHECK(block != nullptr);
578 DCHECK(packed_block != nullptr);
579 uLongf size = tmp_size_;
580 const int result =
581 compress(reinterpret_cast<Bytef*>(tmp_block_.get()), &size,
582 reinterpret_cast<const Bytef*>(block), this->input_size());
583 CHECK_EQ(Z_OK, result);
584 absl::string_view block_str;
585 block_str = absl::string_view(tmp_block_.get(), size);
586 packed_block->assign(block_str.data(), block_str.size());
587 }
588
589 void Unpack(const std::string& packed_block, addrval<T>* block) override {
590 DCHECK(block != nullptr);
591 uLongf size = this->input_size();
592 const int result =
593 uncompress(reinterpret_cast<Bytef*>(block), &size,
594 reinterpret_cast<const Bytef*>(packed_block.c_str()),
595 packed_block.size());
596 CHECK_EQ(Z_OK, result);
597 }
598
599 private:
600 const uint64_t tmp_size_;
601 std::unique_ptr<char[]> tmp_block_;
602 DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(ZlibTrailPacker);
603};
604
605template <class T>
606class CompressedTrail {
607 public:
608 CompressedTrail(
609 int block_size,
610 ConstraintSolverParameters::TrailCompression compression_level)
611 : block_size_(block_size),
612 blocks_(nullptr),
613 free_blocks_(nullptr),
614 data_(new addrval<T>[block_size]),
615 buffer_(new addrval<T>[block_size]),
616 buffer_used_(false),
617 current_(0),
618 size_(0) {
619 switch (compression_level) {
620 case ConstraintSolverParameters::NO_COMPRESSION: {
621 packer_.reset(new NoCompressionTrailPacker<T>(block_size));
622 break;
623 }
624 case ConstraintSolverParameters::COMPRESS_WITH_ZLIB: {
625 packer_.reset(new ZlibTrailPacker<T>(block_size));
626 break;
627 }
628 default: {
629 LOG(ERROR) << "Should not be here";
630 }
631 }
632
633 // We zero all memory used by addrval arrays.
634 // Because of padding, all bytes may not be initialized, while compression
635 // will read them all, even if the uninitialized bytes are never used.
636 // This makes valgrind happy.
637
638 memset(data_.get(), 0, sizeof(*data_.get()) * block_size);
639 memset(buffer_.get(), 0, sizeof(*buffer_.get()) * block_size);
640 }
641 ~CompressedTrail() {
642 FreeBlocks(blocks_);
643 FreeBlocks(free_blocks_);
644 }
645 const addrval<T>& Back() const {
646 // Back of empty trail.
647 DCHECK_GT(current_, 0);
648 return data_[current_ - 1];
649 }
650 void PopBack() {
651 if (size_ > 0) {
652 --current_;
653 if (current_ <= 0) {
654 if (buffer_used_) {
655 data_.swap(buffer_);
656 current_ = block_size_;
657 buffer_used_ = false;
658 } else if (blocks_ != nullptr) {
659 packer_->Unpack(blocks_->compressed, data_.get());
660 FreeTopBlock();
661 current_ = block_size_;
662 }
663 }
664 --size_;
665 }
666 }
667 void PushBack(const addrval<T>& addr_val) {
668 if (current_ >= block_size_) {
669 if (buffer_used_) { // Buffer is used.
670 NewTopBlock();
671 packer_->Pack(buffer_.get(), &blocks_->compressed);
672 // O(1) operation.
673 data_.swap(buffer_);
674 } else {
675 data_.swap(buffer_);
676 buffer_used_ = true;
677 }
678 current_ = 0;
679 }
680 data_[current_] = addr_val;
681 ++current_;
682 ++size_;
683 }
684 int64_t size() const { return size_; }
685
686 private:
687 struct Block {
688 std::string compressed;
689 Block* next;
690 };
691
692 void FreeTopBlock() {
693 Block* block = blocks_;
694 blocks_ = block->next;
695 block->compressed.clear();
696 block->next = free_blocks_;
697 free_blocks_ = block;
698 }
699 void NewTopBlock() {
700 Block* block = nullptr;
701 if (free_blocks_ != nullptr) {
702 block = free_blocks_;
703 free_blocks_ = block->next;
704 } else {
705 block = new Block;
706 }
707 block->next = blocks_;
708 blocks_ = block;
709 }
710 void FreeBlocks(Block* blocks) {
711 while (nullptr != blocks) {
712 Block* next = blocks->next;
713 delete blocks;
714 blocks = next;
715 }
716 }
717
718 std::unique_ptr<TrailPacker<T>> packer_;
719 const int block_size_;
720 Block* blocks_;
721 Block* free_blocks_;
722 std::unique_ptr<addrval<T>[]> data_;
723 std::unique_ptr<addrval<T>[]> buffer_;
724 bool buffer_used_;
725 int current_;
726 int size_;
727};
728} // namespace

730// ----- Trail -----
731
732// Object are explicitly copied using the copy ctor instead of
733// passing and storing a pointer. As objects are small, copying is
734// much faster than allocating (around 35% on a complete solve).
735
736extern void RestoreBoolValue(IntVar* var);
737
738struct Trail {
739 CompressedTrail<int> rev_ints_;
740 CompressedTrail<int64_t> rev_int64s_;
741 CompressedTrail<uint64_t> rev_uint64s_;
742 CompressedTrail<double> rev_doubles_;
743 CompressedTrail<void*> rev_ptrs_;
744 std::vector<IntVar*> rev_boolvar_list_;
745 std::vector<bool*> rev_bools_;
746 std::vector<bool> rev_bool_value_;
747 std::vector<int*> rev_int_memory_;
748 std::vector<int64_t*> rev_int64_memory_;
749 std::vector<double*> rev_double_memory_;
750 std::vector<BaseObject*> rev_object_memory_;
751 std::vector<BaseObject**> rev_object_array_memory_;
752 std::vector<void*> rev_memory_;
753 std::vector<void**> rev_memory_array_;
754
755 Trail(int block_size,
756 ConstraintSolverParameters::TrailCompression compression_level)
757 : rev_ints_(block_size, compression_level),
758 rev_int64s_(block_size, compression_level),
759 rev_uint64s_(block_size, compression_level),
760 rev_doubles_(block_size, compression_level),
761 rev_ptrs_(block_size, compression_level) {}
762
763 void BacktrackTo(StateMarker* m) {
764 int target = m->rev_int_index_;
765 for (int curr = rev_ints_.size(); curr > target; --curr) {
766 const addrval<int>& cell = rev_ints_.Back();
767 cell.restore();
768 rev_ints_.PopBack();
769 }
770 DCHECK_EQ(rev_ints_.size(), target);
771 // Incorrect trail size after backtrack.
772 target = m->rev_int64_index_;
773 for (int curr = rev_int64s_.size(); curr > target; --curr) {
774 const addrval<int64_t>& cell = rev_int64s_.Back();
775 cell.restore();
776 rev_int64s_.PopBack();
777 }
778 DCHECK_EQ(rev_int64s_.size(), target);
779 // Incorrect trail size after backtrack.
780 target = m->rev_uint64_index_;
781 for (int curr = rev_uint64s_.size(); curr > target; --curr) {
782 const addrval<uint64_t>& cell = rev_uint64s_.Back();
783 cell.restore();
784 rev_uint64s_.PopBack();
785 }
786 DCHECK_EQ(rev_uint64s_.size(), target);
787 // Incorrect trail size after backtrack.
788 target = m->rev_double_index_;
789 for (int curr = rev_doubles_.size(); curr > target; --curr) {
790 const addrval<double>& cell = rev_doubles_.Back();
791 cell.restore();
792 rev_doubles_.PopBack();
793 }
794 DCHECK_EQ(rev_doubles_.size(), target);
795 // Incorrect trail size after backtrack.
796 target = m->rev_ptr_index_;
797 for (int curr = rev_ptrs_.size(); curr > target; --curr) {
798 const addrval<void*>& cell = rev_ptrs_.Back();
799 cell.restore();
800 rev_ptrs_.PopBack();
801 }
802 DCHECK_EQ(rev_ptrs_.size(), target);
803 // Incorrect trail size after backtrack.
804 target = m->rev_boolvar_list_index_;
805 for (int curr = rev_boolvar_list_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
806 IntVar* const var = rev_boolvar_list_[curr];
807 RestoreBoolValue(var);
808 }
809 rev_boolvar_list_.resize(target);
810
811 DCHECK_EQ(rev_bools_.size(), rev_bool_value_.size());
812 target = m->rev_bools_index_;
813 for (int curr = rev_bools_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
814 *(rev_bools_[curr]) = rev_bool_value_[curr];
815 }
816 rev_bools_.resize(target);
817 rev_bool_value_.resize(target);
818
819 target = m->rev_int_memory_index_;
820 for (int curr = rev_int_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
821 delete[] rev_int_memory_[curr];
822 }
823 rev_int_memory_.resize(target);
824
825 target = m->rev_int64_memory_index_;
826 for (int curr = rev_int64_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
827 delete[] rev_int64_memory_[curr];
828 }
829 rev_int64_memory_.resize(target);
830
831 target = m->rev_double_memory_index_;
832 for (int curr = rev_double_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
833 delete[] rev_double_memory_[curr];
834 }
835 rev_double_memory_.resize(target);
836
837 target = m->rev_object_memory_index_;
838 for (int curr = rev_object_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
839 delete rev_object_memory_[curr];
840 }
841 rev_object_memory_.resize(target);
842
843 target = m->rev_object_array_memory_index_;
844 for (int curr = rev_object_array_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target;
845 --curr) {
846 delete[] rev_object_array_memory_[curr];
847 }
848 rev_object_array_memory_.resize(target);
849
850 target = m->rev_memory_index_;
851 for (int curr = rev_memory_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
852 // Explicitly call unsized delete
853 ::operator delete(reinterpret_cast<char*>(rev_memory_[curr]));
854 // The previous cast is necessary to deallocate generic memory
855 // described by a void* when passed to the RevAlloc procedure
856 // We cannot do a delete[] there
857 // This is useful for cells of RevFIFO and should not be used outside
858 // of the product
859 }
860 rev_memory_.resize(target);
861
862 target = m->rev_memory_array_index_;
863 for (int curr = rev_memory_array_.size() - 1; curr >= target; --curr) {
864 delete[] rev_memory_array_[curr];
865 // delete [] version of the previous unsafe case.
866 }
867 rev_memory_array_.resize(target);
868 }
869};

1113// Backtrack is implemented using 3 primitives:
1114// CP_TRY to start searching
1115// CP_DO_FAIL to signal a failure. The program will continue on the CP_ON_FAIL
1116// primitive.
1117// Implementation of backtrack using setjmp/longjmp.
1118// The clean portable way is to use exceptions, unfortunately, it can be much
1119// slower. Thus we use ideas from Prolog, CP/CLP implementations,
1120// continuations in C and implement the default failing and backtracking
1121// using setjmp/longjmp. You can still use exceptions by defining
1122// CP_USE_EXCEPTIONS_FOR_BACKTRACK
1123#ifndef CP_USE_EXCEPTIONS_FOR_BACKTRACK
1124// We cannot use a method/function for this as we would lose the
1125// context in the setjmp implementation.
1126#define CP_TRY(search) \
1127 CHECK(!search->jmpbuf_filled_) << "Fail() called outside search"; \
1128 search->jmpbuf_filled_ = true; \
1129 if (setjmp(search->fail_buffer_) == 0)
1130#define CP_ON_FAIL else
1131#define CP_DO_FAIL(search) longjmp(search->fail_buffer_, 1)
1132#else // CP_USE_EXCEPTIONS_FOR_BACKTRACK
1133class FailException {};
1134#define CP_TRY(search) \
1135 CHECK(!search->jmpbuf_filled_) << "Fail() called outside search"; \
1136 search->jmpbuf_filled_ = true; \
1137 try
1138#define CP_ON_FAIL catch (FailException&)
1139#define CP_DO_FAIL(search) throw FailException()
1140#endif // CP_USE_EXCEPTIONS_FOR_BACKTRACK
1141
1142void Search::JumpBack() {
1143 if (jmpbuf_filled_) {
1144 jmpbuf_filled_ = false;
1145 CP_DO_FAIL(this);
1146 } else {
1147 std::string explanation = "Failure outside of search";
1148 solver_->AddConstraint(solver_->MakeFalseConstraint(explanation));
1149 }
1150}

1177void Solver::SetBranchSelector(BranchSelector bs) {
1178 // We cannot use the trail as the search can be nested and thus
1179 // deleted upon backtrack. Thus we guard the undo action by a
1180 // check on the number of nesting of solve().
1181 const int solve_depth = SolveDepth();
1182 AddBacktrackAction(
1183 [solve_depth](Solver* s) {
1184 if (s->SolveDepth() == solve_depth) {
1185 s->ActiveSearch()->SetBranchSelector(nullptr);
1186 }
1187 },
1188 false);
1189 searches_.back()->SetBranchSelector(std::move(bs));
1190}

1192DecisionBuilder* Solver::MakeApplyBranchSelector(BranchSelector bs) {
1193 return RevAlloc(new ApplyBranchSelector(std::move(bs)));
1194}

1286bool Search::AcceptSolution() {
1287 bool valid = true;
1288 for (SearchMonitor* const monitor :
1289 GetEventListeners(Solver::MonitorEvent::kAcceptSolution)) {
1290 if (!monitor->AcceptSolution()) {
1291 // Even though we know the return value, we cannot return yet: this would
1292 // break the contract we have with solution monitors. They all deserve
1293 // a chance to look at the solution.
1294 valid = false;
1295 }
1296 }
1297 return valid;

1307 // a chance to look at the solution.

1455void Solver::Init() {
1456 CheckSolverParameters(parameters_);
1457 queue_ = std::make_unique<Queue>(this);
1458 trail_ = std::make_unique<Trail>(parameters_.trail_block_size(),
1459 parameters_.compress_trail());
1460 state_ = OUTSIDE_SEARCH;
1461 branches_ = 0;
1462 fails_ = 0;
1463 decisions_ = 0;
1464 neighbors_ = 0;
1465 filtered_neighbors_ = 0;
1466 accepted_neighbors_ = 0;
1467 optimization_direction_ = NOT_SET;
1468 timer_ = std::make_unique<ClockTimer>();
1469 searches_.assign(1, new Search(this, 0));
1470 fail_stamp_ = uint64_t{1};
1471 balancing_decision_ = std::make_unique<BalancingDecision>();
1472 fail_intercept_ = nullptr;
1473 true_constraint_ = nullptr;
1474 false_constraint_ = nullptr;
1475 fail_decision_ = std::make_unique<FailDecision>();
1476 constraint_index_ = 0;
1477 additional_constraint_index_ = 0;
1478 num_int_vars_ = 0;
1479 propagation_monitor_.reset(BuildTrace(this));
1480 local_search_monitor_.reset(BuildLocalSearchMonitorPrimary(this));
1481 print_trace_ = nullptr;
1482 anonymous_variable_index_ = 0;
1483 should_fail_ = false;
1484
1485 for (int i = 0; i < kNumPriorities; ++i) {
1486 demon_runs_[i] = 0;
1487 }
1488 searches_.push_back(new Search(this));
1489 PushSentinel(SOLVER_CTOR_SENTINEL);
1490 InitCachedIntConstants(); // to be called after the SENTINEL is set.
1491 InitCachedConstraint(); // Cache the true constraint.
1492 timer_->Restart();
1493 model_cache_.reset(BuildModelCache(this));
1494 AddPropagationMonitor(reinterpret_cast<PropagationMonitor*>(demon_profiler_));
1495 AddLocalSearchMonitor(
1496 reinterpret_cast<LocalSearchMonitor*>(local_search_profiler_));
1497}

1499Solver::~Solver() {
1500 // solver destructor called with searches open.
1501 CHECK_EQ(2, searches_.size());
1502 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
1503
1504 StateInfo info;
1505 Solver::MarkerType finalType = PopState(&info);
1506 // Not popping a SENTINEL in Solver destructor.
1507 DCHECK_EQ(finalType, SENTINEL);
1508 // Not popping initial SENTINEL in Solver destructor.
1509 DCHECK_EQ(info.int_info, SOLVER_CTOR_SENTINEL);
1510 gtl::STLDeleteElements(&searches_);
1511 DeleteDemonProfiler(demon_profiler_);
1512 DeleteLocalSearchProfiler(local_search_profiler_);
1513}

1597void Solver::PushState(Solver::MarkerType t, const StateInfo& info) {
1598 StateMarker* m = new StateMarker(t, info);
1599 if (t != REVERSIBLE_ACTION || info.int_info == 0) {
1600 m->rev_int_index_ = trail_->rev_ints_.size();
1601 m->rev_int64_index_ = trail_->rev_int64s_.size();
1602 m->rev_uint64_index_ = trail_->rev_uint64s_.size();
1603 m->rev_double_index_ = trail_->rev_doubles_.size();
1604 m->rev_ptr_index_ = trail_->rev_ptrs_.size();
1605 m->rev_boolvar_list_index_ = trail_->rev_boolvar_list_.size();
1606 m->rev_bools_index_ = trail_->rev_bools_.size();
1607 m->rev_int_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_int_memory_.size();
1608 m->rev_int64_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_int64_memory_.size();
1609 m->rev_double_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_double_memory_.size();
1610 m->rev_object_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_object_memory_.size();
1611 m->rev_object_array_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_object_array_memory_.size();
1612 m->rev_memory_index_ = trail_->rev_memory_.size();
1613 m->rev_memory_array_index_ = trail_->rev_memory_array_.size();
1614 }
1615 searches_.back()->marker_stack_.push_back(m);
1616 queue_->increase_stamp();
1617}
1618
1619void Solver::AddBacktrackAction(Action a, bool fast) {
1620 StateInfo info(std::move(a), fast);
1621 PushState(REVERSIBLE_ACTION, info);
1622}
1623
1624Solver::MarkerType Solver::PopState(StateInfo* info) {
1625 CHECK(!searches_.back()->marker_stack_.empty())
1626 << "PopState() on an empty stack";
1627 CHECK(info != nullptr);
1628 StateMarker* const m = searches_.back()->marker_stack_.back();
1629 if (m->type_ != REVERSIBLE_ACTION || m->info_.int_info == 0) {
1630 trail_->BacktrackTo(m);
1631 }
1632 Solver::MarkerType t = m->type_;
1633 (*info) = m->info_;
1634 searches_.back()->marker_stack_.pop_back();
1635 delete m;
1636 queue_->increase_stamp();
1637 return t;
1638}

1640void Solver::check_alloc_state() {
1641 switch (state_) {
1642 case OUTSIDE_SEARCH:
1643 case IN_ROOT_NODE:
1644 case IN_SEARCH:
1645 case NO_MORE_SOLUTIONS:
1646 case PROBLEM_INFEASIBLE:
1647 break;
1648 case AT_SOLUTION:
1649 LOG(FATAL) << "allocating at a leaf node";
1650 default:
1651 LOG(FATAL) << "This switch was supposed to be exhaustive, but it is not!";
1652 }
1653}

1687void Solver::AddConstraint(Constraint* const c) {
1688 DCHECK(c != nullptr);
1689 if (c == true_constraint_) {
1690 return;
1691 }
1692 if (state_ == IN_SEARCH) {
1693 queue_->AddConstraint(c);
1694 } else if (state_ == IN_ROOT_NODE) {
1695 DCHECK_GE(constraint_index_, 0);
1696 DCHECK_LE(constraint_index_, constraints_list_.size());
1697 const int constraint_parent =
1698 constraint_index_ == constraints_list_.size()
1699 ? additional_constraints_parent_list_[additional_constraint_index_]
1700 : constraint_index_;
1701 additional_constraints_list_.push_back(c);
1702 additional_constraints_parent_list_.push_back(constraint_parent);
1703 } else {
1704 if (parameters_.print_added_constraints()) {
1705 LOG(INFO) << c->DebugString();
1706 }
1707 constraints_list_.push_back(c);
1708 }
1709}
1710
1711void Solver::AddCastConstraint(CastConstraint* const constraint,
1712 IntVar* const target_var, IntExpr* const expr) {
1713 if (constraint != nullptr) {
1714 if (state_ != IN_SEARCH) {
1715 cast_constraints_.insert(constraint);
1716 cast_information_[target_var] =
1717 Solver::IntegerCastInfo(target_var, expr, constraint);
1718 }
1719 AddConstraint(constraint);
1720 }
1721}

1723void Solver::Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const {
1724 visitor->BeginVisitModel(name_);
1725 ForAll(constraints_list_, &Constraint::Accept, visitor);
1726 visitor->EndVisitModel(name_);

1728
1729void Solver::ProcessConstraints() {
1730 // Both constraints_list_ and additional_constraints_list_ are used in
1731 // a FIFO way.
1732 if (parameters_.print_model()) {
1733 ModelVisitor* const visitor = MakePrintModelVisitor();
1734 Accept(visitor);
1735 }
1736 if (parameters_.print_model_stats()) {
1737 ModelVisitor* const visitor = MakeStatisticsModelVisitor();
1738 Accept(visitor);
1739 }
1740
1741 if (parameters_.disable_solve()) {
1742 LOG(INFO) << "Forcing early failure";
1743 Fail();
1744 }
1745
1746 // Clear state before processing constraints.
1747 const int constraints_size = constraints_list_.size();
1748 additional_constraints_list_.clear();
1749 additional_constraints_parent_list_.clear();
1750
1751 for (constraint_index_ = 0; constraint_index_ < constraints_size;
1752 ++constraint_index_) {
1753 Constraint* const constraint = constraints_list_[constraint_index_];
1754 propagation_monitor_->BeginConstraintInitialPropagation(constraint);
1755 constraint->PostAndPropagate();
1756 propagation_monitor_->EndConstraintInitialPropagation(constraint);
1757 }
1758 CHECK_EQ(constraints_list_.size(), constraints_size);
1759
1760 // Process nested constraints added during the previous step.
1761 for (int additional_constraint_index_ = 0;
1762 additional_constraint_index_ < additional_constraints_list_.size();
1763 ++additional_constraint_index_) {
1764 Constraint* const nested =
1765 additional_constraints_list_[additional_constraint_index_];
1766 const int parent_index =
1767 additional_constraints_parent_list_[additional_constraint_index_];
1768 Constraint* const parent = constraints_list_[parent_index];
1769 propagation_monitor_->BeginNestedConstraintInitialPropagation(parent,
1770 nested);
1771 nested->PostAndPropagate();
1772 propagation_monitor_->EndNestedConstraintInitialPropagation(parent, nested);
1773 }
1774}

1871
1872// Opens a new top level search.
1873void Solver::NewSearch(DecisionBuilder* const db,
1874 const std::vector<SearchMonitor*>& monitors) {
1875 // TODO(user) : reset statistics
1876
1877 CHECK(db != nullptr);
1878 const bool nested = state_ == IN_SEARCH;
1879
1880 if (state_ == IN_ROOT_NODE) {
1881 LOG(FATAL) << "Cannot start new searches here.";
1882 }
1883
1884 Search* const search = nested ? new Search(this) : searches_.back();
1885 search->set_created_by_solve(false); // default behavior.
1886
1887 // ----- jumps to correct state -----
1888
1889 if (nested) {
1890 // Nested searches are created on demand, and deleted afterwards.
1891 DCHECK_GE(searches_.size(), 2);
1892 searches_.push_back(search);
1893 } else {
1894 // Top level search is persistent.
1895 // TODO(user): delete top level search after EndSearch().
1896 DCHECK_EQ(2, searches_.size());
1897 // TODO(user): Check if these two lines are still necessary.
1898 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
1899 state_ = OUTSIDE_SEARCH;
1900 }
1901
1902 // ----- manages all monitors -----
1903
1904 // Always install the main propagation and local search monitors.
1905 propagation_monitor_->Install();
1906 if (demon_profiler_ != nullptr) {
1907 InstallDemonProfiler(demon_profiler_);
1908 }
1909 local_search_monitor_->Install();
1910 if (local_search_profiler_ != nullptr) {
1911 InstallLocalSearchProfiler(local_search_profiler_);
1912 }
1913
1914 // Push monitors and enter search.
1915 for (SearchMonitor* const monitor : monitors) {
1916 if (monitor != nullptr) {
1917 monitor->Install();
1918 }
1919 }
1920 std::vector<SearchMonitor*> extras;
1921 db->AppendMonitors(this, &extras);
1922 for (SearchMonitor* const monitor : extras) {
1923 if (monitor != nullptr) {
1924 monitor->Install();
1925 }
1926 }
1927 // Install the print trace if needed.
1928 // The print_trace needs to be last to detect propagation from the objective.
1929 if (nested) {
1930 if (print_trace_ != nullptr) { // Was installed at the top level?
1931 print_trace_->Install(); // Propagates to nested search.
1932 }
1933 } else { // Top level search
1934 print_trace_ = nullptr; // Clears it first.
1935 if (parameters_.trace_propagation()) {
1936 print_trace_ = BuildPrintTrace(this);
1937 print_trace_->Install();
1938 } else if (parameters_.trace_search()) {
1939 // This is useful to trace the exact behavior of the search.
1940 // The '######## ' prefix is the same as the progagation trace.
1941 // Search trace is subsumed by propagation trace, thus only one
1942 // is necessary.
1943 SearchMonitor* const trace = MakeSearchTrace("######## ");
1944 trace->Install();
1945 }
1946 }
1947
1948 // ----- enters search -----
1949
1950 search->EnterSearch();
1951
1952 // Push sentinel and set decision builder.
1953 PushSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
1954 search->set_decision_builder(db);
1955}
1956
1957// Backtrack to the last open right branch in the search tree.
1958// It returns true in case the search tree has been completely explored.
1959bool Solver::BacktrackOneLevel(Decision** const fail_decision) {
1960 bool no_more_solutions = false;
1961 bool end_loop = false;
1962 while (!end_loop) {
1963 StateInfo info;
1964 Solver::MarkerType t = PopState(&info);
1965 switch (t) {
1966 case SENTINEL:
1967 CHECK_EQ(info.ptr_info, this) << "Wrong sentinel found";
1968 CHECK((info.int_info == ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL && SolveDepth() == 1) ||
1969 (info.int_info == INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL && SolveDepth() > 1));
1970 searches_.back()->sentinel_pushed_--;
1971 no_more_solutions = true;
1972 end_loop = true;
1973 break;
1974 case SIMPLE_MARKER:
1975 LOG(ERROR) << "Simple markers should not be encountered during search";
1976 break;
1977 case CHOICE_POINT:
1978 if (info.int_info == 0) { // was left branch
1979 (*fail_decision) = reinterpret_cast<Decision*>(info.ptr_info);
1980 end_loop = true;
1981 searches_.back()->set_search_depth(info.depth);
1982 searches_.back()->set_search_left_depth(info.left_depth);
1983 }
1984 break;
1985 case REVERSIBLE_ACTION: {
1986 if (info.reversible_action != nullptr) {
1987 info.reversible_action(this);
1988 }
1989 break;
1990 }
1991 }
1992 }
1993 Search* const search = searches_.back();
1994 search->EndFail();
1995 fail_stamp_++;
1996 if (no_more_solutions) {
1997 search->NoMoreSolutions();
1998 }
1999 return no_more_solutions;
2000}
2001
2002void Solver::PushSentinel(int magic_code) {
2003 StateInfo info(this, magic_code);
2004 PushState(SENTINEL, info);
2005 // We do not count the sentinel pushed in the ctor.
2006 if (magic_code != SOLVER_CTOR_SENTINEL) {
2007 searches_.back()->sentinel_pushed_++;
2008 }
2009 const int pushed = searches_.back()->sentinel_pushed_;
2010 DCHECK((magic_code == SOLVER_CTOR_SENTINEL) ||
2011 (magic_code == INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL && pushed == 1) ||
2012 (magic_code == ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL && pushed == 2));
2013}
2014
2015void Solver::RestartSearch() {
2016 Search* const search = searches_.back();
2017 CHECK_NE(0, search->sentinel_pushed_);
2018 if (SolveDepth() == 1) { // top level.
2019 if (search->sentinel_pushed_ > 1) {
2020 BacktrackToSentinel(ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL);
2021 }
2022 CHECK_EQ(1, search->sentinel_pushed_);
2023 PushSentinel(ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL);
2024 state_ = IN_SEARCH;
2025 } else {
2026 CHECK_EQ(IN_SEARCH, state_);
2027 if (search->sentinel_pushed_ > 0) {
2028 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2029 }
2030 CHECK_EQ(0, search->sentinel_pushed_);
2031 PushSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2032 }
2033
2034 search->RestartSearch();
2035}

2037// Backtrack to the initial search sentinel.
2038// Does not change the state, this should be done by the caller.
2039void Solver::BacktrackToSentinel(int magic_code) {
2040 Search* const search = searches_.back();
2041 bool end_loop = search->sentinel_pushed_ == 0;
2042 while (!end_loop) {
2043 StateInfo info;
2044 Solver::MarkerType t = PopState(&info);
2045 switch (t) {
2046 case SENTINEL: {
2047 CHECK_EQ(info.ptr_info, this) << "Wrong sentinel found";
2048 CHECK_GE(--search->sentinel_pushed_, 0);
2049 search->set_search_depth(0);
2050 search->set_search_left_depth(0);
2051
2052 if (info.int_info == magic_code) {
2053 end_loop = true;
2054 }
2055 break;
2056 }
2057 case SIMPLE_MARKER:
2058 break;
2059 case CHOICE_POINT:
2060 break;
2061 case REVERSIBLE_ACTION: {
2062 info.reversible_action(this);
2063 break;
2064 }
2065 }
2066 }
2067 fail_stamp_++;
2068}
2069
2070// Closes the current search without backtrack.
2071void Solver::JumpToSentinelWhenNested() {
2072 CHECK_GT(SolveDepth(), 1) << "calling JumpToSentinel from top level";
2073 Search* c = searches_.back();
2074 Search* p = ParentSearch();
2075 bool found = false;
2076 while (!c->marker_stack_.empty()) {
2077 StateMarker* const m = c->marker_stack_.back();
2078 if (m->type_ == REVERSIBLE_ACTION) {
2079 p->marker_stack_.push_back(m);
2080 } else {
2081 if (m->type_ == SENTINEL) {
2082 CHECK_EQ(c->marker_stack_.size(), 1) << "Sentinel found too early";
2083 found = true;
2084 }
2085 delete m;
2086 }
2087 c->marker_stack_.pop_back();
2088 }
2089 c->set_search_depth(0);
2090 c->set_search_left_depth(0);
2091 CHECK_EQ(found, true) << "Sentinel not found";
2092}

2122// Search for the next solution in the search tree.
2123bool Solver::NextSolution() {
2124 Search* const search = searches_.back();
2125 Decision* fd = nullptr;
2126 const int solve_depth = SolveDepth();
2127 const bool top_level = solve_depth <= 1;
2128
2129 if (solve_depth == 0 && !search->decision_builder()) {
2130 LOG(WARNING) << "NextSolution() called without a NewSearch before";
2131 return false;
2132 }
2133
2134 if (top_level) { // Manage top level state.
2135 switch (state_) {
2136 case PROBLEM_INFEASIBLE:
2137 return false;
2138 case NO_MORE_SOLUTIONS:
2139 return false;
2140 case AT_SOLUTION: {
2141 if (BacktrackOneLevel(&fd)) { // No more solutions.
2142 state_ = NO_MORE_SOLUTIONS;
2143 return false;
2144 }
2145 state_ = IN_SEARCH;
2146 break;
2147 }
2148 case OUTSIDE_SEARCH: {
2149 state_ = IN_ROOT_NODE;
2150 search->BeginInitialPropagation();
2151 CP_TRY(search) {
2152 ProcessConstraints();
2153 search->EndInitialPropagation();
2154 PushSentinel(ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL);
2155 state_ = IN_SEARCH;
2156 search->ClearBuffer();
2157 }
2158 CP_ON_FAIL {
2159 queue_->AfterFailure();
2160 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2161 state_ = PROBLEM_INFEASIBLE;
2162 return false;
2163 }
2164 break;
2165 }
2166 case IN_SEARCH: // Usually after a RestartSearch
2167 break;
2168 case IN_ROOT_NODE:
2169 LOG(FATAL) << "Should not happen";
2170 break;
2171 }
2172 }
2173
2174 volatile bool finish = false;
2175 volatile bool result = false;
2176 DecisionBuilder* const db = search->decision_builder();
2177
2178 while (!finish) {
2179 CP_TRY(search) {
2180 if (fd != nullptr) {
2181 StateInfo i1(fd, 1, search->search_depth(),
2182 search->left_search_depth()); // 1 for right branch
2183 PushState(CHOICE_POINT, i1);
2184 search->RefuteDecision(fd);
2185 branches_++;
2186 fd->Refute(this);
2187 // Check the fail state that could have been set in the python/java/C#
2188 // layer.
2189 CheckFail();
2190 search->AfterDecision(fd, false);
2191 search->RightMove();
2192 fd = nullptr;
2193 }
2194 Decision* d = nullptr;
2195 for (;;) {
2196 search->BeginNextDecision(db);
2197 d = db->Next(this);
2198 search->EndNextDecision(db, d);
2199 if (d == fail_decision_.get()) {
2200 Fail(); // fail now instead of after 2 branches.
2201 }
2202 if (d != nullptr) {
2203 DecisionModification modification = search->ModifyDecision();
2204 switch (modification) {
2205 case SWITCH_BRANCHES: {
2206 d = RevAlloc(new ReverseDecision(d));
2207 // We reverse the decision and fall through the normal code.
2208 ABSL_FALLTHROUGH_INTENDED;
2209 }
2210 case NO_CHANGE: {
2211 decisions_++;
2212 StateInfo i2(d, 0, search->search_depth(),
2213 search->left_search_depth()); // 0 for left branch
2214 PushState(CHOICE_POINT, i2);
2215 search->ApplyDecision(d);
2216 branches_++;
2217 d->Apply(this);
2218 CheckFail();
2219 search->AfterDecision(d, true);
2220 search->LeftMove();
2221 break;
2222 }
2223 case KEEP_LEFT: {
2224 search->ApplyDecision(d);
2225 d->Apply(this);
2226 CheckFail();
2227 search->AfterDecision(d, true);
2228 break;
2229 }
2230 case KEEP_RIGHT: {
2231 search->RefuteDecision(d);
2232 d->Refute(this);
2233 CheckFail();
2234 search->AfterDecision(d, false);
2235 break;
2236 }
2237 case KILL_BOTH: {
2238 Fail();
2239 }
2240 }
2241 } else {
2242 break;
2243 }
2244 }
2245 if (search->AcceptSolution()) {
2246 search->IncrementSolutionCounter();
2247 if (!search->AtSolution() || !CurrentlyInSolve()) {
2248 result = true;
2249 finish = true;
2250 } else {
2251 Fail();
2252 }
2253 } else {
2254 Fail();
2255 }
2256 }
2257 CP_ON_FAIL {
2258 queue_->AfterFailure();
2259 if (search->should_finish()) {
2260 fd = nullptr;
2261 BacktrackToSentinel(top_level ? ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL
2262 : INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2263 result = false;
2264 finish = true;
2265 search->set_should_finish(false);
2266 search->set_should_restart(false);
2267 // We do not need to push back the sentinel as we are exiting anyway.
2268 } else if (search->should_restart()) {
2269 fd = nullptr;
2270 BacktrackToSentinel(top_level ? ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL
2271 : INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2272 search->set_should_finish(false);
2273 search->set_should_restart(false);
2274 PushSentinel(top_level ? ROOT_NODE_SENTINEL : INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2275 search->RestartSearch();
2276 } else {
2277 if (BacktrackOneLevel(&fd)) { // no more solutions.
2278 result = false;
2279 finish = true;
2280 }
2281 }
2282 }
2283 }
2284 if (result) {
2285 search->ClearBuffer();
2286 }
2287 if (top_level) { // Manage state after NextSolution().
2288 state_ = (result ? AT_SOLUTION : NO_MORE_SOLUTIONS);
2289 }
2290 return result;
2291}
2292
2293void Solver::EndSearch() {
2294 Search* const search = searches_.back();
2295 if (search->backtrack_at_the_end_of_the_search()) {
2296 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2297 } else {
2298 CHECK_GT(searches_.size(), 2);
2299 if (search->sentinel_pushed_ > 0) {
2300 JumpToSentinelWhenNested();
2301 }
2302 }
2303 search->ExitSearch();
2304 search->Clear();
2305 if (2 == searches_.size()) { // Ending top level search.
2306 // Restores the state.
2307 state_ = OUTSIDE_SEARCH;
2308 // Checks if we want to export the profile info.
2309 if (!parameters_.profile_file().empty()) {
2310 const std::string& file_name = parameters_.profile_file();
2311 LOG(INFO) << "Exporting profile to " << file_name;
2312 ExportProfilingOverview(file_name);
2313 }
2314 if (parameters_.print_local_search_profile()) {
2315 const std::string profile = LocalSearchProfile();
2316 if (!profile.empty()) LOG(INFO) << profile;
2317 }
2318 } else { // We clean the nested Search.
2319 delete search;
2320 searches_.pop_back();
2321 }
2322}
2323
2324bool Solver::CheckAssignment(Assignment* const solution) {
2325 CHECK(solution);
2326 if (state_ == IN_SEARCH || state_ == IN_ROOT_NODE) {
2327 LOG(FATAL) << "CheckAssignment is only available at the top level.";
2328 }
2329 // Check state and go to OUTSIDE_SEARCH.
2330 Search* const search = searches_.back();
2331 search->set_created_by_solve(false); // default behavior.
2332
2333 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2334 state_ = OUTSIDE_SEARCH;
2335
2336 // Push monitors and enter search.
2337 search->EnterSearch();
2338
2339 // Push sentinel and set decision builder.
2340 DCHECK_EQ(0, SolveDepth());
2341 DCHECK_EQ(2, searches_.size());
2342 PushSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2343 search->BeginInitialPropagation();
2344 CP_TRY(search) {
2345 state_ = IN_ROOT_NODE;
2346 DecisionBuilder* const restore = MakeRestoreAssignment(solution);
2347 restore->Next(this);
2348 ProcessConstraints();
2349 search->EndInitialPropagation();
2350 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2351 search->ClearBuffer();
2352 state_ = OUTSIDE_SEARCH;
2353 return true;
2354 }
2355 CP_ON_FAIL {
2356 const int index =
2357 constraint_index_ < constraints_list_.size()
2358 ? constraint_index_
2359 : additional_constraints_parent_list_[additional_constraint_index_];
2360 Constraint* const ct = constraints_list_[index];
2361 if (ct->name().empty()) {
2362 LOG(INFO) << "Failing constraint = " << ct->DebugString();
2363 } else {
2364 LOG(INFO) << "Failing constraint = " << ct->name() << ":"
2365 << ct->DebugString();
2366 }
2367 queue_->AfterFailure();
2368 BacktrackToSentinel(INITIAL_SEARCH_SENTINEL);
2369 state_ = PROBLEM_INFEASIBLE;
2370 return false;
2371 }
2372}

2477// --- Propagation object names ---
2478
2479std::string Solver::GetName(const PropagationBaseObject* object) {
2480 const std::string* name = gtl::FindOrNull(propagation_object_names_, object);
2481 if (name != nullptr) {
2482 return *name;
2483 }
2484 const IntegerCastInfo* const cast_info =
2485 gtl::FindOrNull(cast_information_, object);
2486 if (cast_info != nullptr && cast_info->expression != nullptr) {
2487 if (cast_info->expression->HasName()) {
2488 return absl::StrFormat("Var<%s>", cast_info->expression->name());
2489 } else if (parameters_.name_cast_variables()) {
2490 return absl::StrFormat("Var<%s>", cast_info->expression->DebugString());
2491 } else {
2492 const std::string new_name =
2493 absl::StrFormat("CastVar<%d>", anonymous_variable_index_++);
2494 propagation_object_names_[object] = new_name;
2495 return new_name;
2496 }
2497 }
2498 const std::string base_name = object->BaseName();
2499 if (parameters_.name_all_variables() && !base_name.empty()) {
2500 const std::string new_name =
2501 absl::StrFormat("%s_%d", base_name, anonymous_variable_index_++);
2502 propagation_object_names_[object] = new_name;
2503 return new_name;
2504 }
2505 return empty_name_;
2506}

2508void Solver::SetName(const PropagationBaseObject* object,
2509 const std::string& name) {
2510 if (parameters_.store_names() &&
2511 GetName(object) != name) { // in particular if name.empty()
2512 propagation_object_names_[object] = name;
2513 }
2514}

2517 return propagation_object_names_.contains(

2519 (!object->BaseName().empty() && parameters_.name_all_variables());
2520}

2860void ModelVisitor::VisitInt64ToBoolExtension(Solver::IndexFilter1 filter,
2861 int64_t index_min,
2862 int64_t index_max) {
2863 if (filter != nullptr) {
2864 std::vector<int64_t> cached_results;
2865 for (int i = index_min; i <= index_max; ++i) {
2866 cached_results.push_back(filter(i));
2867 }
2868 BeginVisitExtension(kInt64ToBoolExtension);
2869 VisitIntegerArgument(kMinArgument, index_min);
2870 VisitIntegerArgument(kMaxArgument, index_max);
2871 VisitIntegerArrayArgument(kValuesArgument, cached_results);
2872 EndVisitExtension(kInt64ToBoolExtension);
2873 }
2874}

2878 CHECK(eval != nullptr);
2879 std::vector<int64_t> cached_results;
2880 for (int i = index_min; i <= index_max; ++i) {
2881 cached_results.push_back(eval(i));
2882 }
2883 BeginVisitExtension(kInt64ToInt64Extension);
2884 VisitIntegerArgument(kMinArgument, index_min);
2885 VisitIntegerArgument(kMaxArgument, index_max);
2886 VisitIntegerArrayArgument(kValuesArgument, cached_results);
2887 EndVisitExtension(kInt64ToInt64Extension);
2888}

3283ProfiledDecisionBuilder::ProfiledDecisionBuilder(DecisionBuilder* db)
3284 : db_(db), name_(db_->GetName()), seconds_(0) {}
3285
3286Decision* ProfiledDecisionBuilder::Next(Solver* const solver) {
3287 timer_.Start();
3288 solver->set_context(name());
3289 // In case db_->Next() fails, gathering the running time on backtrack.
3290 solver->AddBacktrackAction(
3291 [this](Solver* solver) {
3292 if (timer_.IsRunning()) {
3293 timer_.Stop();
3294 seconds_ += timer_.Get();
3295 }
3296 solver->set_context("");
3297 },
3298 true);
3299 Decision* const decision = db_->Next(solver);
3300 timer_.Stop();
3301 seconds_ += timer_.Get();
3302 return decision;
3303}

3330void Constraint::Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const {
